	Type Casting:
	Type casting is converting the type of data from one data type to another. We have 2 types of Type Casting.

	1) Explicit/Narrowing/Manual  2) Implicit/Widening/Automatic

	When we go from a bigger data type to a smaller one it is called explicit/narrowing/Manual and when we go from a smaller data type
	to a larger data type we call it Implicit/widening/Automatic.

  Amount of Bytes in these Data Types:
	byte(8) 
	short(16) 
	char(16) 
	int(32) 
	long(64)
	float(32) 
	Double(64)
	
	Implicit/Widening/Automatic
	byte-->short-->char-->int-->long-->float-->Double
	
	Explicit/narrowing/Manual
	byte-<-short<--char<--int<--long<--float<--Double
	
	Why we need type casting?
	When we are working in teams we might need to convert data from different data types.
	WHen we are working with math sometimes we need to get rid of decimal part as we are only intrested in the non-decimal part.
	
	What is the Syntax?
	
	Explicit/narrowing/manual
	int box=1000;
	byte box2=(byte) box;
	
	Implicit/Widening/Automatic
	short box1=250;
	int box2=box1;
